        <author>
            <name>Marcus Cazzola</name>
        </author>
        <link href="https://cazzola.click/beat-saber-remake.html"/>
        <id>https://cazzola.click/beat-saber-remake.html</id>
        <media:content url="https://cazzola.click/media/posts/6/beat_saber_no_top.gif" medium="image" />
            <category term="Personal Projects"/>

        <updated>2023-03-22T09:48:28+01:00</updated>
            <summary>
                <![CDATA[
                        <img src="https://cazzola.click/media/posts/6/beat_saber_no_top.gif" alt="Beat saber image" />
                    Details: Made in Unity with C#. Inspired by Beat Saber. Custom level creation tool to create new levels fast. Fast&hellip;
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                    <p><img src="https://cazzola.click/media/posts/6/beat_saber_no_top.gif" class="type:primaryImage" alt="Beat saber image" /></p>
                <h5><strong>Details:</strong></h5>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Made in Unity with C#.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Inspired by Beat Saber.</span></li>
<li aria-level="1">Custom level creation tool to create new levels fast.</li>
</ul>
<figure class="post__video"><br><iframe loading="lazy" width="447" height="250" style="width: 447px; height: 250px;" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Zx0YP4zVIF0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" data-mce-fragment="1"></iframe></figure>
<p><strong>Fast level creation tool:</strong></p>
<p>In the normal Beat Saber, every cube is placed out manually by hand to make a level. This makes the level creation, of one song, take many hours.</p>
<figure class="post__image"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://cazzola.click/media/posts/6/beat-saber-level-normal-editor.PNG" alt="" width="253" height="142" sizes="(min-width: 37.5em) 1600px, 80vw" srcset="https://cazzola.click/media/posts/6/responsive/beat-saber-level-normal-editor-xs.PNG 384w ,https://cazzola.click/media/posts/6/responsive/beat-saber-level-normal-editor-sm.PNG 600w ,https://cazzola.click/media/posts/6/responsive/beat-saber-level-normal-editor-md.PNG 768w ,https://cazzola.click/media/posts/6/responsive/beat-saber-level-normal-editor-lg.PNG 1200w ,https://cazzola.click/media/posts/6/responsive/beat-saber-level-normal-editor-xl.PNG 1600w"></figure>
<p>I created a tool that lets the developer “records” a song. The developer records the song by swinging his sabers and pressing the trigger button. Then the position, time, color, and sword travel direction gets stored in a file. Then the file can get played back and someone can play the level.</p>
<figure class="post__video"><iframe loading="lazy" width="560" height="314" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/V6AphRKWRGA" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" data-mce-fragment="1"></iframe></figure>
<p> </p>
            ]]>
        </content>
